text.0:
A Facebook post with a photo of a fuel station in flames claiming it was set ablaze during protests over the arrest of presidential candidate Robert Kyagulany, on November 18 is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The station burnt down in September: https://t.co/xvmScZOVHZ
text.1:
An image featured in an article claiming to show tyres that were set ablaze on a road in Uganda is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:camera_with_flash: The photo was taken in August 2017 during protests in Gauteng, South Africa: https://t.co/F5hlD8u96R
text.2:
A Facebook post claiming that US president-elect Joe Biden has endorsed Kenya’s Deputy President William Ruto’s presidential bid is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: Neither office has confirmed such an endorsement, and there has not been any media coverage of this claim: https://t.co/aGFrOnIeBj
text.3:
A Facebook post claiming that the Huduma Namba card is renewable every three years is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The card has no expiry date and provides each person with a unique identifying number for use when transacting with the Kenya government: https://t.co/o8MlwbAmTB
